l line of argument critically informed by gender studies and intersectionality, post-colonialism, geopolitics, and game studies. This book looks at who develops, localizes, and consumes games, problematizing play as a diverse and contested transnational domain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aComputer gamesxSocial aspectszDeveloping countries. 0aComputer games. 0aGamesxData processing. 0aMobile gamesxSocial aspectszDeveloping countries. 0aMobile games. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aGame Studies. 4aMedia Studies. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aART / Video Game Art.2bisacsh  aGames for Change, Latin American Art, Mobile Players, Game Piracy, Global South.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048543946zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048543946423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048543946/original  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070478-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Des